Khan attended a ‘thanksgiving’ political rally held by President Uhuru Kenyatta and Dr Ruto in April 2016 to “celebrate” the “termination” of the Kenya cases.Khan even addressed the rally, at which President Kenyatta stated he will not allow any other Kenyan to be tried in a foreign court. For the first time, there was voting to elect the Prosecutor of the International Criminal Court (ICC) last Friday. This was the culmination of a months-long disjointed and flawed process that failed to achieve consensus on the appointment of Fatou Bensouda’s successor by the Assembly of States Parties (ASP) — the 123 state signatories of the Rome Statute, the ICC’s founding treaty. 



