Hobbled by the very predictable need to recuse himself in important current and possible future cases on the Kenya situation, the new ICC prosecutor faces an uphill battle in winning the support and confidence of critical sectors of the court’s stakeholders, which could have been avoided by a clear and irreproachable process. 

Ms Otieno is the Executive Director of the Africa Centre for Open Governance (AfriCOG). gladwellotieno@gmail.com. The seven injured scribes were covering opposition leader Bobi Wine when they were set upon by security forces. The National Assembly is on a collision course with the Executive following her appointment to South Korea. The new system has been designed by the Ministry of Information, Communications and Technology.